advertisementList.advertisementDescription:
Perfectly positioned in this popular coastal suburb, surrounded by stunning residences, this much loved home has been held in the same family since it was built approximately 50 years ago. With a solid full brick construction throughout and a superb practical floorplan that will suit the growing family, the home lends itself to huge potential and is set on a large 658sqm level block.
Enjoying a central location close to beaches, coastal walks and shops, it is also only one block to South Coogee Public School.
- Four generous bedrooms (three with built-ins)
- Spacious main with walk in robe and ensuite
- Large retro kitchen with ample cupboard space
- Sundrenched North East facing terrace
- Formal and informal living/dining rooms
- Additional family room/rumpus room
- Large level rear yard with IG pool, fantastic for entertaining
- Four car garage with internal access
- Large laundry with washing chute
- Additional workshop and storage facility
- Sweeping district views
- Offered for the first time in 50 years!
Council Rates:  $647 pq approx
Water Rates:  $191 pq approx
Land Size:  658 sqm approx
Inspection: Thursday & Saturday 11.45am   12.30pm
Auction: Saturday 12th August 2017 at 11.30am
Venue: On Site
Website: ngfarah.com.au
Agents: Martin Farah 0418 402 015
